<th valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Mean Time Gaps (N)</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">25</td>
<td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">13.6 ±14.0</td>
<td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">10.4 ± 10.8</td>
<td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">3.1 ± 3.6<a href="#fn1-2976958" class="usa-link"><sup>*</sup></a>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">2.0 ± 2.7</td>
</tr></tbody>
</table></div>
<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/t2-2976958/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div>
<div class="tw-foot p">
<div class="fn" id="_fn_p42"><p><strong><a href="#t2-2976958" class="usa-link">Table 2</a>:</strong> Reports the number of self-report EHR time use intervals recorded, the average amount of self-reported time, the average amount of time these intervals took calculated by our method, the difference between the two methods, and the average number of gaps in the audit log for each interval. In most cases calculated time was less than reported time due to gaps in the audit log where no activities were recorded during minutes. The p value was calculated with a paired t test.</p></div>
<div class="fn" id="fn1-2976958">
<sup>*</sup><p class="display-inline">p&lt;.001</p>
</div>
</div></section></section><section id="sec3_3"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">Overall EHR usage</h3>
